      "response": {
        "answer": "You should request PTO at least **10 business days** in advance. However, if there are emergencies, your manager may approve an exception to this rule. \n\nSource: our employee handbook",
        "citations": [
          {
            "text": "## Time off and leave\n\n### Paid time off (PTO)\n\nFull-time employees accrue **PTO** according to the accrual schedule published on the internal HR portal. PTO requests must be submitted **at least 10 business days** in advance unless your manager approves an exception for emergencies.\n\nUnused PTO may roll over up to **5 days** into the next calendar year unless local policy states otherwise.",
